{
  "texts": [
    "All the test subjects demonstrated normal or corrected-to-normal visual capabilities.",
    "The average age was 22.4 years and the median age was 22 years, with a minimum age of 19 years and a maximum age of 27 years.",
    "Data processingThe subjective visual quality scores collected with the DSIS protocol were first analyzed for outliers using the methodology proposed in ITU-R Recommendations BT.500 [52].",
    "The analysis did not reveal any outliers, and therefore the scores of all 20 test subjects were used for the analysis.",
    "The raw scores were processed by computing the Mean Opinion Score (MOS) and 95% confidence intervals (CI) according to a Student's t-distribution.For the PWC experiment, the preference probability for each stimulus in the stimuli pairs was computed by dividing the number of received votes by the total number of test subjects."
  ]
}